 see are or are becoming. What philosophy wants from images, Rodowick shows, is to renew itself conceptually through deep engagement with new forms of aesthetic experience.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aAesthetics. 0aMotion picturesxSocial aspects. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / General.2bisacsh  aChristian Metz.  aGilles Deleuze.  aHarun Farocki.  aStanley Cavell.  aVictor Burgin.  adigital or virtual images.  alogic of sensation.  amemory of cinema.  amoving image installation.  aphotography and belief.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831107119360 cprintz978022651305840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226513225423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226513225/original  a978-3-11-071193-6  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles